class Solution {
    public String robotWithString(String s) {
        int n = s.length();
        int[] freq = new int[26];
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) freq[c - 'a']++;

        StringBuilder t = new StringBuilder();
        StringBuilder res = new StringBuilder();
        int i = 0;
        while (i < n || t.length() > 0) {
            if (t.length() == 0) {
                t.append(s.charAt(i++));
                freq[s.charAt(i - 1) - 'a']--;
                continue;
            }
            char minNext = 'z';
            for (int k = 0; k < 26; k++) {
                if (freq[k] > 0) {
                    minNext = (char) ('a' + k);
                    break;
                }
            }
            char last = t.charAt(t.length() - 1);
            if (last <= minNext) {
                res.append(last);
                t.setLength(t.length() - 1);
            } else {
                t.append(s.charAt(i));
                freq[s.charAt(i) - 'a']--;
                i++;
            }
        }
        return res.toString();
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n * 26)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Greedy simulation using a frequency array to know the smallest remaining character in O(26) per step; append to t until the top of t is the smallest possible, then pop to the result.

